author: suat
msg: It is not mandatory for a ContentItem to have a textual content part i.e a content part having one of the TEXT_HTML, TEXT_PLAIN or TEXT_XML media types. If it has a binary content only the binary content of the ContentItem is stored but not indexed. A StoreException is thrown only if the ContentItem does have neither a textual content part or any binary content.
